                "tab_row_KLaPxi": {
                  "type": "_tab-row",
                  "name": "Tab row",
                  "settings": {
                    "heading": "What Is UV Ink?",
                    "content": "<p>UVDTF (Ultraviolet Direct-to-Film) printing is an advanced printing technology that allows high-resolution, full-color designs to be transferred onto various surfaces with exceptional durability. Unlike traditional printing methods, UVDTF printing utilizes ultraviolet (UV) light to cure specially formulated inks, creating vibrant and long-lasting prints.</p><p>The texture you feel on the cup is the top layer of UV ink called varnish. The varnish gives the designs their glossy appearance.</p><p><strong>Our UV prints are not stickers. </strong>Stickers are smaller, individually cut designs printed on various materials (vinyl, paper, or polyester) with an adhesive backing for easy peel-and-stick application. Stickers are remove-able, and do not last.</p>",
                    "page": "",
                    "liquid": "",
